Directed Graphs



Not always possible to put into linear ordering




Prove any DAG can be linearly ordered
Think about Last Vertex


Repeat...
Sink is Dead End
Cycle indicates we don't have a DAG
This algorithm is O( v^2 )
Can speed up by retracing path instead of starting over.
i.e. take one step back after removing a sink. (basically a DFS)


D is source vertex (no way to get back),
G not reachable from A
F is a sink vertex (no way to leave)


Can't get back to A from C, D or I
SCC = Strongly Connected Components
